ns:common.topic.description: JEAN was a dialect of the JOSS programming language developed for and used on ICT 1900 series computers in the late 1960s and early 1970s; it was implemented under the MINIMOP operating system. It was used at the University of Southampton.\nJEAN was an acronym derived from \"JOSS Extended and Adapted for Nineteen-hundred\". It was operated from a Teletype terminal.
